# .aidocs/reingest-system.aidocs - /reingest Contract

Purpose
- Refresh memory with an explicit ingestion scope chosen by the user.
- Serve as the primary ingestion command surface.

When to use
- Memory appears stale or inconsistent with recent code changes.
- User wants controlled ingestion depth before continuing work.

Contract
- `/reingest` MUST start by asking one targeted question with these options:
  1) `full-reingest` - analyse full project and rebuild docs/memory mapping.
  2) `git-reingest` - analyse staged/unstaged/untracked changes and update memory from changed files only.
  3) `date-reingest` - analyse newest modified files since the NOW checkpoint date and update memory incrementally.
  4) Type your own answer.
- After the user picks a mode, run only that mode.
- Use merge/edit semantics in memory files (no duplicate append-only growth).
- Keep user-authored memory content intact unless explicitly asked to rewrite it.
- Log notable outcomes in today's daily file.

Mode semantics
- `full-reingest`: broad discovery + topic-map rebuild + canonical memory refresh.
- `git-reingest`: use git status/diff/untracked set as source-of-truth for file selection.
- `date-reingest`: derive baseline from `/.MEMORY/NOW.md` checkpoint/date markers, then select files modified after baseline.
- In all modes, if project root `FIXES_BY_OTHER_AGENTS.md` exists, merge relevant entries into `/.MEMORY/related-projects/FIXES_BY_OTHER_AGENTS.md`.

Guardrails
- Never store secrets.
- If mode cannot be executed deterministically (missing baseline/date or no git metadata), STOP and ask for fallback mode.
